Write a program that when runs, reads input typed the user and quits only when user types a ‘quit’ character.

Ans:

While True:

    User_input = input(“Type something (type ‘quit’ to exit): “)

    if user_input.lower() == ‘quit’:

        print(“Exiting program.”)

        break

    else:

        print(f”You typed: {user_input}”)


Output:
Type something (type ‘quit’ to exit): quit
Exiting program.
[Program finished]
